\pard\f0\fs28  Subsp.{\b  bansagensis} (H. Wagner) Soó, {\i Syn. Syst. Geobot. Fl. Veg. Hung.}{\b  4}: 174 (1970) ({\i C. bansagensis} H. Wagner), from Romania, is like {\b 189}({\b b}) but has the leaves densely arachnoid-lanate, the middle cauline leaves lanceolate or elliptical, the involucre 14-18 × 12-14 mm and brown, recurved appendages; subsp. joannis Karpati, {\i Borbásia}{\b  5-6}: 92 (1946), described from N.W. Jugoslavia, is like {\b 189}({\b c}) but has the leaves wider and shorter, the lower leaves green and the upper mostly lanate, clustered capitula and the involucre c. 10 × 3-4 mm; the status of both these taxa is uncertain.
