\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 190. C. indurata} Janka, {\i Flora} ({\i Regensb}.) {\b 41}: 444 (1858). Perennial. Stems 50-80(-100) cm, erect, sparingly branched. Leaves greyish-arachnoid-hairy, undivided, broadly lanceolate; lower dentate, acute, attenuate into the petiole; middle attenuate or rounded at the base. Capitulum solitary. Involucre 15 × 8-10 mm, ovoid or ovoid-cylindrical; appendages not completely covering bracts, dark brown, black at the base, narrowly lanceolate, attenuate into a subulate-filiform, recurved, pectinate fimbriate, black acumen 6-7 mm, the fimbriae 8-12 on each side, pale brown, the middle ones 3 mm. Florets pinkish-orange or purple, the outer radiate. Achenes c. 3 mm; pappus very short. {\i Grassland and open woods. • From E. Czechoslovakia to Bulgaria.} Bu Cz Hu Rm.
\par 

