\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b uniflora}: Stems simple, rarely branched. Leaves white-tomentose, entire; lower oblong-lanceolate, gradually attenuate into the petiole; middle cauline lanceolate. Involucre 17-22 mm in diameter, subglobose; appendages covering bracts.{\i  Pastures and rocky places in montane regions. S.W. Alps}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b nervosa} (Willd.) Bonnier & Layens,{\i  Fl. Fr.} 180 (1894) ({\i C. nervosa }Willd.): Stems erect, usually simple, with one capitulum. Leaves green, puberulent, dentate or sinuate-dentate; lower oblong-ovate, truncate at the base, hastate or auriculate-semiamplexicaul; upper narrowly elliptical. Involucre 18-20(-25) mm in diameter, ovoid-globose; appendages covering bracts. 2n = 22.{\i  Throughout the range of the species}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b ferdinandi} (Gren.) Bonnier,{\i  Fl. Compl. Fr.}{\b  6}: 45 (1923): Like subsp. ({\b b}) but stems ascending, branched; lower leaves sinuately lobed; capitula numerous; appendages not completely covering bracts.{\i  S.W. & S.C. Alps}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b dandoni} (Urum.) Dostál,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  71}: 208 (1976) ({\i C. davidovii} Urum.,{\i  C. nervosa} subsp. {\i davidovii} (Urum.) Hayek): Stems branched. Leaves green, puberulent, entire; lower elliptical, gradually attenuate into the petiole; upper lanceolate, rounded at base. Involucre 12 mm in diameter, ovoid-cylindrical; appendages completely covering bracts. {\i Bulgaria} ({\i Stara Planina}).
\par 

