\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 192. C. kernerana} Janka,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  22}: 178 (1872) ({\i C. derventana} Janka, non Vis. & Pancic). Perennial. Stems 10-40 cm, simple or with 2 branches, ascending. Leaves green, subglabrous or hispidulous, scabrid; lower lanceolate, dentate, pinnatifid or pinnatilobed, attenuate into a petiole; uppermost oblong or ovate-lanceolate, sometimes subamplexicaul. Involucre 15 × 15-18 mm; appendages attenuate into a triangular-lanceolate, blackish, filiform, plumose-fimbriate, arcuate-recurved acumen up to 8 mm. Florets purple, the outer radiate. Achenes c. 4 mm; pappus 2-4 mm.{\i  Mountain rocks. • Bulgaria.} Bu.
